Premise.
Airing in December 2014, Ascension follows an alternate reality in which, 
in 1963, President Kennedy and the government sent 600 volunteers (men, 
women, and children) into space on a century-long voyage aboard a 
self-sustaining generation ship, and consists of six 40 minute episodes.

During celebrations of the 51st year of its 100 year journey through space, 
a murder occurs among those aboard the U.S. Orion Class spaceship Ascension, 
with the body of Lorelei Wright found on the ship's poolside "beach." 
Captain William Denninger asks Executive Officer Aaron Gault to investigate.
